    {
      "id": "sybil_10_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_10",
      "description": "This 2004 Porsche 911 Carrera (996.2) features the refined 3.6L M96/03 naturally aspirated flat-six, delivering 315 hp through a precise 6-speed G96 manual transaxle. The chassis remains taut with factory-spec McPherson struts up front and a multi-link rear setup, offering superb lateral grip and communicative steering. Crucially, the IMS bearing has been retrofitted with a dual-row ceramic solution, and the rear main seal (RMS) was replaced during the same service interval to ensure long-term reliability. The cooling system has been proactively refreshed with a high-flow water pump and low-temp thermostat to mitigate thermal stress. Finished in Arctic Silver, this 911 exhibits honest patina consistent with its driver-quality status but remains mechanically robust and ready for the canyon or the track.",
